# Cybersecurity Resources for Beginners

Breaking into cybersecurity can be overwhelming with so many paths and specializations. This guide provides essential resources to help you get started.

## 📚 Books
- **"The Web Application Hacker's Handbook"** – Dafydd Stuttard & Marcus Pinto
- **"Cybersecurity Essentials"** – Charles J. Brooks
- **"Hacking: The Art of Exploitation"** – Jon Erickson
- **"Blue Team Handbook: Incident Response Edition"** – Don Murdoch
- **"Metasploit: The Penetration Tester’s Guide"** – David Kennedy et al.

## 🖥 Free Online Courses
- [Cybrary](https://www.cybrary.it/) – Free and paid cybersecurity courses
- [Coursera (Introduction to Cybersecurity by NYU)](https://www.coursera.org/learn/intro-cyber-security)
- [Open Security Training](https://opensecuritytraining.info/) – Free advanced security courses
- [SANS Cyber Aces](https://www.cyberaces.org/) – Free foundational security training
- [TryHackMe (Beginner Labs)](https://tryhackme.com/)

## 🏆 Certifications (Beginner-Friendly)
- **CompTIA Security+** – Entry-level security certification
- **Certified in Cybersecurity (CC) - ISC2** – Free beginner certification
- **Google Cybersecurity Certificate** – Great for career starters
- **CompTIA CySA+** – For those interested in Blue Team (Defensive Security)
- **eJPT (eLearnSecurity Junior Penetration Tester)** – Entry-level penetration testing

## 💻 Hands-on Labs & Practice
- [Hack The Box (HTB)](https://www.hackthebox.com/) – Labs for penetration testing
- [TryHackMe](https://tryhackme.com/) – Gamified cybersecurity learning
- [OverTheWire](https://overthewire.org/) – Wargames for security learning
- [CTFtime](https://ctftime.org/) – List of cybersecurity Capture The Flag (CTF) competitions
- [RangeForce Community Edition](https://www.rangeforce.com/) – Hands-on blue team exercises

## 📰 Blogs & News
- [Krebs on Security](https://krebsonsecurity.com/)
- [Schneier on Security](https://www.schneier.com/)
- [Dark Reading](https://www.darkreading.com/)
- [The Hacker News](https://thehackernews.com/)
- [Bleeping Computer](https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/)

